      "text": "been unmarked indicating it is currently waiting time sheet approval from a manager or authorized personnel. The calculated summary displays, what this is is it takes the time entered by the employee, puts it through the in for WFM rule engine and calculates how the employee should be paid for the hours entered. In this case, we just have a standard 40 hour work week. We set functionality exists on the time sheet to allow users to fill out time sheets in a more expeditious manner. You can populate the time sheet as the same as last week, where you can save the time as a preset. I'll go ahead and save this time sheet as a standard work week preset. Advancing forward to the next week, I can now use that preset that I've just saved. You'll see the time sheet is automatically populated based on the settings in that preset. At any point in a way can go back to their time sheet in the current paper to add additional hours. I'll do that now. Adding an additional hour for Friday. Once I click save, I can see that additional hour in the calculated summary as calm. It defaults a comp. However, an employee can use the comp override functionality to elect to be paid directly for that hour. Indicate the amount of hours you'd like to override and click save. And you'll now notice in the calculate summary that the regular work performed with an hour type of OT1.5 will be paid out to the employee rather than being comped. Optionally print functionality is available to print time sheets as needed. And that is the conclusion of our time sheet demo. Thank you.",
